  "body": "### Subject of the issue\r\n**@truffle/codec@0.7.1** requires **underscore@1.9.1**, which has a security problem (see: [**CVE-2021-23358**](https://snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JS-UNDERSCORE-1080984)):\r\n`@truffle/codec@0.7.1 ➔ web3-utils@1.2.9 ➔ underscore@1.9.1`\r\n\r\nI do not know if this vulnerability actually affects **@truffle/codec**, but it will show up in security reports about dependencies. Since a large number of developers still use **@truffle/codec@0.7.\\***([7,280 downloads per week](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@truffle/codec/v/0.7.1?activeTab=versions)), is there any posibility that you could release an update version for 0.7.\\* (ie **0.7.2**) that introduces a patched version(**>=1.12.1<1.13.0-0  or >=1.13.0-2**) of **underscore**?\r\n\r\n   In **@truffle/codec@0.7.2**, maybe you can perform the following update (not crossing major version):\r\n     `web3-utils 1.2.9 ➔ 1.3.6`\r\nwhere `web3-utils@1.3.6 ➔ underscore@1.12.1`, and **underscore@1.12.1** has fixed the vulnerability [**CVE-2021-23358**](https://snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JS-UNDERSCORE-1080984).\r\nThank you for your contributions.",
